cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with autonomous exploration by a robot in an unknown environment. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of Hilbert maps, which are a type of image-based representation of the environment. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper formulates exploration as a variational problem and uses functional gradient methods for optimisation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper uses mutual information as a metric for optimisation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with controlling the motion of a robot in an unknown environment.
